    "from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "x = np.arange(5)\n",
    "money = [26, 29, 16, 11, 19]\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def millions(x, pos):\n",
    "    return '% ' + str(x)\n",
    "\n",
    "formatter = FuncFormatter(millions)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,7))\n",
    "ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(formatter)\n",
    "for i in range(len(x)):\n",
    "    ax.text(i-0.15, money[i]-2, str(money[i])+ '%', color='White')\n",
    "plt.bar(x, money)\n",
    "plt.xticks(x, ('18-24', '25-34', '35-44', '45-54', '+55'))\n",
    "plt.figtext(.5,.05,'Share of Spotify users in the United States as of March 2018, by age',fontsize=12,ha='center')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(7, 7), subplot_kw=dict(aspect=\"equal\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "recipe = [\"35 % Europe\",\"27 % North America\",\n",
    "          \"22 % Latin America\", \"16 % Rest of World\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "data = [float(x.split()[0]) for x in recipe]\n",
    "ingredients = [x.split()[-1] for x in recipe]\n",
    "\n",
    "def func(pct, allvals):\n",
    "    index = 0\n",
    "    for i in range(len(data)):\n",
    "        if \"{:.1f}\".format(pct) == '{:.1f}'.format(data[i]):\n",
    "            index = i\n",
    "            \n",
    "    country = ingredients[index]\n",
    "    return \"{:.1f}%\\n({:s})\".format(pct, country)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "wedges, texts, autotexts = ax.pie(data, autopct=lambda pct: func(pct, data),\n",
    "                                  textprops=dict(color=\"w\"))\n",
    "\n",
    "ax.legend(wedges, ingredients,\n",
    "          title=\"Ingredients\",\n",
    "          loc=\"center left\",\n",
    "          bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.setp(autotexts, size=10, weight=\"bold\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# ax.set_title(\"Total MAUs by Region\")\n",
    "plt.figtext(.5,.05,'Share of Spotify users in the United States as of March 2018, by age',fontsize=12,ha='center')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
